  "text": "The analysis here is a longitudinal intra-seasonal case study of the post-vaccination B cell repertoire in a subject exposed to a novel, egg-adapted HA derived from pandemic H1N1 influenza. Our relatively extensive sampling has allowed us to follow the rise and fall of clonal lineages within the post-vaccination season and to assess which antigenic sites on the pandemic vaccine generated the most potent responses. Previous work has shown that both Ab and T cell responses arise rapidly in response to a single dose of adjuvanted vaccine and that recall of imprinted immune memory dominates [CITATION_1] .",
